    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "These are metrics I usually look at before a release:\r\n- Lodestar - validator monitor: prev epoch miss ratio, wrong head ratio\r\n- VM + host: Heap + external memory, process memory, gc, CPU Usage of lodestar\r\n- Lodestar/general: number of peers, average number of mesh peers for attestation subnet topic\r\n- Lodestar - networking: all metrics in summary part, Gossip validation queue: job time, dropped job, Gossip Block Received Delay, Gossip block process time\r\n- Lodestar - debug gossipsub: Peer count per gossip score threshold, Attnet count with >0 mesh peers, Gossip RPCs transmitted / sec\r\n- Lodestar - block processor: Rate of blocks being set as head after 4s\r\n\r\nNeed inputs from others as well to finalize the list before implementing",
